caption: Hidden gem! The casual and quaint ambiance matches the delicious comfort food. Loved the shrimp and grits!  The chicken looked fabulous. Can’t wait to try it next time around. Such a great brunch find!
Very limited vegetarian option for lunch. Non-alcoholic drink is limited. Garden is pretty nice.
The service was really slow. Our reservation was at 1330 and we had been waiting for 60 minutes for our food to come out
Wonderful service, delicious food! Lovely atmosphere, great for friends to catch up and chat
Loved the vibe for upstairs dining. All safety precautions were followed. Excellent food.

BEST chicken and waffles we’ve ever had, and I’m from South Carolina. I know southern food really well; this place was amazing. We had the server Juan, and he made our experience phenomenal. The kitchen was pretty behind, and he made everything right. He has such a peaceful, genuine, and laid back spirit. Loved the atmosphere as well. The peach mimosas are lovely.
Food, service, and ambiance were all fantastic.  Also tables were spaced far apart and everyone was masking so it seemed fairly safe.
They’re fried chicken is dope
Lovely, great food,  Dominique (our server) was a delight.
Have been 2 times now - Was just okay each time  Beet salad good - fried chx is the special and good texture but rather bland  It’s not bad per se, just kind of a let down
Food was great! Unfortunately, it was bitter cold on Christmas day so we were so fidgety and it was difficult to enjoy the meal.
Fun outdoor heated patio with fun foods! Decor was festive and relaxing!
Cozy and beautiful interiors. I love the fried chicken!

We came here for lunch, and we were seated in tents. While the heaters were not warm enough for us the decor was nice. We waited a while for the food. We ordered the gnocchi, pierogi, and the fried chicken. Everything tested great with good  flavors but the portions were small. Nice experience but we were still hungry after it.

The outdoor patio they’ve created to follow the Covid guidelines is cozy and warm! The food was delicious and the service was also wonderful. We tried a lot of things but they are known for their fried chicken and it did not disappoint. Whatever the hot sauce was that they use was incredible I wish I bought some to go!! Tasty drinks and had a great time, highly recommend.
Hummingbird was the best!!
Great atmosphere even in the outdoor tent. Food was very good and the staff very friendly
Patio was beautifully decorated for the holidays and was perfectly warm on a cold night. Food was delicious as always.

ONE OF THE BEST RESTAURANTS IN CHICAGO!! There handing COVID super well! Check temperature, provide hand sanitizer and have heated, outdoor tent seating. It was so comfortable and warm. We came here after trying to sit at another restaurant in downtown and it was just too unbearably cold because there heaters weren’t even working, so we came to Blue Door. And everything was SO good. Get the max and cheese, any of their salads or sandwiches to be honest. All the food is so fresh and good. The service is great and the patio seating was so warm with the heaters and decorated nicely for the holidays. We sat outside on a cold day.. it was literally 30 degrees out but it felt so warm and comfortable with the heated patio tent seating. I love this place and will keep coming back!

Great place for lunch and dinner. Sad part is their kitchen closes at 8 pm. Good Wine and Hard Liquor collection. They have Appetizers, Entrees, Burgers and Sandwiches, Sides and Desserts.  It’s located on Clark And Elm in Gold Coast.
Great food for a weekend lunch.  They have a tent outside, cleaning everything, and spacing people out!

We ate here on 12/4/20 and it was so delicious!!! While I would have preferred to eat inside in the super cute dining room, the tent was comfortable and they've decorated it wonderfully.  We started with 2 architectural cocktails that were tasty, unique and so well presented.  For dinner we had the fried chicken plate, shrimp & grits and a side of mac'n'cheese.  For all my hot sauce lovers out there, ask for a side because its to die for.  The friend chicken skin was perfection, the chicken was so juicy, it was incredible.  The shrimp were perfectly cooked, the grits made me feel like I was in Georgia, the whole thing was phenomenal! Our server was wonderful, he was also the bartender.  I'm so glad they're busy and able to stay open during covid.  Support these guys, you won't regret it!!
Nice patio but extremely limited lunch options for vegetarians and probably nothing on offer for vegans. Service was disappointing especially given the 6% COVID charge.
The friend chicken and hot sauce, delicious enough said.
The fried buttermilk chicken is cooked to perfection and so crispy.

An amazing experience start to finish from service to the food. We ordered the deviled eggs, brussel sprout salad, fried chicken and hummingbird cake based on the waiter Max’s recommendation. It was perfect in every way! I highly encourage everyone to try this & can’t wait to come back myself! 5/5 just isn’t enough!

Interior was 10 out of 10 Food was not worth that much money but it was more than average. We ordered burger and waffle and chicken for main. Burger was not cooked at all it was all pink inside. They offered us solutions but we did not have enough time. Chicken and waffle, 3 pieces of chicken and regular American waffle. Other than that delicious. Coffee was good and drink was good.
Delicious food (chicken and waffles a standout) in a comfortable and cultured outdoor seating area.

I had the salmon en croute and it was without a doubt the best dish I had in the city (to date). I was lucky to have chef Emilo cook this well thought out  dish. Accompanied by a wonderful server named Isidra. HIGHLY recommend; a wonderful atmosphere and a caring staff will undoubtedly yield a great night and a great time.

Very nice place, great atmosphere, good service, great food and reasonable prices.  Went for brunch with friends during the weekend. You can reserve a table and you have a 30 minutes before you loose it. Important to note that they didn't answer the phone, so if you are a bit late you can't really let them know. Also you need the whole party to be shown to your table.  Service and food were wonderful. We ordered the cornbread (the fruits and cream was so good) and Hemingway cake to share, and I also took the  fried Chicken sandwich (doesn't look that good but actually really tasty).  Covid-19: Outdoor seating in a cute patio feels very Covid safe. The staff wear masks and gloves, but they are not too harsh with people who already at the table (for example: they will not ask you to put on a mask when delivering food to the table- usually). QR code for the menus before seated, but you can also find it at their website. Do do take Covid-19 fees (which I think shouldn't be something the customer is paying for).  Overall although one or two issues, I think this place is great.
Pretty outdoor patio with proper soc. dist. Service well trained and impeccable. Simple menu. Each dish a delight. Order the key lime pie!
This is a $12 salad...looks soggy and more like $2. Never ordering here again.
Limited choice for dinner. I guess it's a Covid thing.

Firs time in Blue Door Kitchen, was a great adventure, outdoor seatings are so comfortable and nicely tucked in. Had crab cake for app, excellent presentation and taste. After that I had burger which had a LOT of garlic aioli (nice taste but too much, burger was impossible to finish, so heavy) omelette was great, service was great as well. Don't agree with 6% Covid surcharge. But I'll be back to this place only when it's nice weather so I can enjoy in garden.
Food is good, not great. Overpriced. Why would you charge $2 for an ice cube? Or a 6% covid surcharge. BS. Will not be back, you probably shouldn't come.
Mediocre at best, food was just ok. Service was just ok... Clean, good spacing, comfortable environment, charges covid 6% fee..
Garden is lovely. Crab cake delicious for lunch.

Their food is amazing, not expensive at all when you compare it to other restaurants in the area. Limited seasonal menu so preview before you go. Service could use a a little improvement. But food makes up for everything! Perfect for a date or dinner with friends.
Noiiiiicee
Amazing patio. Excellent staff and coffee. The food was ok but the atmosphere here makes you forget where you are. Very welcoming staff.
They charged me $2.... for ice with my whiskey... 🙄  Other than that it was a really cute place with a nice patio. Food was great too! But that's pretty ridiculous..
The food is absolutely amazing. Our server was attentive and helpful.

Food was good and patio was amazing. Only thing that we didn’t like was slow not really caring service and horrible cocktails . We ordered Moscow mule and margarita (margarita was missing triple sec and lime juce) and Moscow mule was so easy on vodka like almost non alcoholic. When we get a check we have been charged 35$ before tax for 2 drinks because our server  ring top shelf liquor even if we didn’t ask for it .
This place is the spot very friendly customer service. Good excellent and drinks are fantastic!! Will definitely come back during the weekend for my Bloody Mary!!😊
Great food and really cute ambiance. Recommend the coffee and key lime pie. Our waiter Maksym was really nice !
Very cute and vibrant atmosphere. The staff were very friendly and accommodating to what we needed. I definitely would recommend coming here!
Beautiful atmosphere & extremely friendly staff! Food is awesome as well. Outdoor garden is amazing & perfectly set up for social distancing! 10/10!!!

The food, place and service were ALL excellent! HOWEVER, you lose a star 🌟 for charging and extra 6% for COVID-19. You should be thankful that customers are still willing to come in and eat. I get it as a business owner, but I'm not here to make you a profit....
Great food and atmosphere.  The fried chicken was excellent.  The drinks fun. The outside seating was nice and relaxing.  I would definitely recommend and dine here again

We had made a reservation well in advance, and when we came in, the hostess seated us inside which was disappointing. We asked if there was any availability outside and she said no without even checking. No other group was seated inside for the course of our entire meal, and a couple that came in immediately after us (a group of 2) was seated outside without a wait, as was every other group that came in that afternoon. It was a wholly depressing meal being the only people sitting inside on a nice sunny day, at a restaurant known for their beautiful outdoor patio.

My reservation was specifically made for outdoor seating, they did not respect this and was told that outside seating would be available with a wait time of 1 hour.  There was no acknowledgement for this error or an apology, which made everything worse.

First time going here.  Food was excellent ..we waited close to a hour and our food we otferd did not come.  Our young waitress did not come and tell us why or even come ask us if we needed anything to drink, water , coffee.  We finally called out to her to find out that there was something wrong electrically and our food was not yet made.  Mind you my 2yr old grandson was with us and now hes starving and its now 2pm.  We finally called out and asked if we could be served some water cofee etc.  The manager ( Felix ) came up to us by this point and apologized sincerely and said the food was on them which was very kind of him.  Meanwhile the waitress still did not come and ask if we needed anything while we waited..  The bottom line is the food is excellent .. The management is great.  They just need to train the waitress's for better customer service..

This was a truly wonderful experience!  The Blue Door Kitchen feels like Art Smith invited us into his home for dinner. The food was exactly like my mom would make but elevated so delightfully.  The deviled eggs were delicious.  The scallops were cooked to perfection.  The fried chicken was crunchy and juicy.  We finished off this feast with Art's Hummingbird Cake which was light and moist. First off, my first time here for Valentine's day and it was incredible.  Our waiter Emanuel was sweet as a button  And gave us impeccable service. Let me start by saying, the Brussel and kale salad has got to be one of the best I have ever eaten in my life. The scallops were amazing, the pork belly was so tasty and the short rib was incredible as well. Not too salty, perfect in taste. Great Manhattan's!  I heard their Fried Chicken is excellent and cannot wait to come back.

Had to wait over 30 mins past the set reservation time to get seated. Food portions were too small. And the “market vegetables” was a repulsive dish of beets mixed with shiitake mushrooms which lacked flavor and I could hardly stomach, and I’m not a picky eater. Would not come again.

Quaint spot, with awesome tea house vibes. It's the epitome of dining in a garden. The staff is nice. The service is good. The food is great. I attended during restaurant week for brunch (such a great deal, 3-courses for $24). The cocktails are fantastic. The food was delicious (the fried chicken is amazing). The beignets are a little different, but still good.
Food is just alright. Tried the brunch for restaurant week and I've definitely had better. Very cute ambiance though.

I used to LOVE and CRAVE Blue Door. We went back this past Sunday for brunch (1/27/18) and was sadly disappointed. They must have gotten a new chef because they no longer had Beignets! It’s was restaurant week and they did offer them with the special menu, but the ones they served to my friend who ordered them were certainly not the light, airy, fluffy ones we were used to getting! We used to order them as soon as we sat down and would devour the little clouds covered in powdered sugar in record time. But they no longer exist. I also ordered my go-to favoraitevthere of the classic ham eggs Benedict, but it was so different! They used to spread a pepper ha of some sort into the muffin before topping it with the ham/eggs/hollandaise, but there was no such thing any more. It was just your basic eggs Benedict. My husband ordered the chicken and waffles and was pleased with it, but we won’t go back. Not sure why they would make such drastic changes to a flawless menu. Too bad.
Beautiful hidden gem. Very cozy, good service, and excellent cuisine.

Amazing spot for dinner.  I had the dumplings and crabcakes as well as the short ribs and mac and cheese. I also had the chocolate terrine to finish which was rich and decadent.  All the food was amazing but my favorite was the fork tender short ribs that melted in your mouth with every bite!!

I ordered a BDK drink and a BDK burger (it came with a very generous amount of cheese that's not my taste but it was two patties so that was nice). My fabulous company ordered soup with sandwich and a fried chicken with bacon sandwich respectively. We all agree the food was delicious and the staff was attentive without being pretentious. Also, the owners aren't from Chicago for those who got triggered by the acronym.  0.5 star removed for street parking which rounds up to 1 full star removal.  They're a member of "top nosh hospitality Chicago" Google it.

Blue Door Kitchen & Garden restaurant is the heart of Chicago’s Gold Coast. The outdoor garden area is magical on a warm day. The dining room is very comfortable and well designed. Their food is perfecte as like made home style cuisine. Food are of classic American dishes such as fried chicken, salads and sandwiches. There have many delicious food item for Lunch and Dinner. Everything was fresh and perfectly prepared with high quality ingredients. Price is reasonable. Service is excellent, friendly and attentive. From GKN SECRET SHOPPER.

I was extremely excited to try this farm-to-table restaurant, but unfortunately I was very disappointed. We had a reservation for four people for dinner. From the beginning, the server had bad attitude and was unpleasant to deal with. The service was below par. Although they close at 11pm, they started giving us dirty looks around 10pm. We felt extremely rushed and unwelcome. The server grabbed plates from the table without asking if we finished eating. She was standing right near our table with her hands crossed just waiting for us to leave. She gave us the bill without us asking for it. She just placed it on the table out of nowhere, and without asking if we wanted split bills. The food was overpriced, especially for its average quality. I do not think that I will be returning to this place, and would not recommend it to others.

I really love the interior design here, it’s so chic and unique. It’s a bit expensive but worths. It’s not crowded in general which makes me surprised.

My family is quite large and ordered multiple things on the menu. I'll list them in order of "most favorite" to "still good": Chicken and Waffles (crispy skin and delicious syrup), Eggs Benedict (great portion and perfectly cooked eggs), Grits (my dad said they were the best he has had), Buttermilk Pancake (cinnamon apples were a good touch), BDK omelet (cooked well, nothing over the top), Side of Bacon (little crispy).  Great atmosphere and service. Thanks, Oscar!

Great burger. I can see why it won the burger contest whose name I don't remember last year. And usually I don't get into the intricate cocktails that have become so popular. Most of the time when people get all fancy with booze, I'm like "Artisan? More like Fartisan!" and then I make armpit toots, but their cocktails were really great and the bartender really was a craftsman. I'd better be careful with using words like craftsman. It's going to make me want to grow a really gross beard, wear vests, and drink Pabst but not like I normally drink Pabst because I'm cheap, only ironically. Speaking of which, I did think it was a little pricey, but I think everything is a little pricey. Most stuff is though.
